description._content: Description: Mother Aleppo Pine trees about 60 years old, previously pruned, standing over self-sown seedlings. Kardaldagh Forest, Elevation 2,600 feet above sea level. Location: Cyprus Date: 1920-1939 Description: Mother Aleppo Pine trees about 60 years old, previously pruned, standing over self-sown seedlings, near main track through Kardaldagh Forest, South side of Range, Elevation 2,600 ft. Location: Cyprus Date: 1920-1939 Our Catalogue Reference: Part of CO 1069/698 This image is part of the Colonial Office photographic collection held at The National Archives.
